[
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"690871\">Chad Nester</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/229199-learning.3A-questions/topic/Constructing.20a.20rack.20from.20a.20shelf.2E/near/605986652\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>I've encountered a binary operation that, somewhat unexpectedly, forms a right-shelf. That is, satisfies the equation: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>⊙</mo><mi>b</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>⊙</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>⊙</mo><mi>c</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>⊙</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>⊙</mo><mi>c</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(a \\odot b) \\odot c = (a \\odot c) \\odot (b \\odot c)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⊙</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">b</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⊙</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⊙</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⊙</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">b</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⊙</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>. </p>\n<p>The potential connection to knot theory is intriguing, and I'm interested to know if it can be made into a <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/rack\">rack</a> in a sensible way.</p>\n<p>Is anything known about this?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I've never seen anyone study the free rack on a shelf - and since they're both rather little-studied algebraic structures, there might not have been any study of this.  </p>\n<p>But both shelves and racks can be described as algebras of Lawvere theories if we include an additional operation in the definition of a shelf, rather than stating the extra clause as a mere property.   I made sure the <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/rack#definition\">nLab article</a> does this.  And I believe that whenever we have two Lawvere theories <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>T</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T&#x27;</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, with the latter having more operations and/or equations than the former, the map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>→</mo><msup><mi>T</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T \\to T&#x27;</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> gives rise to a functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>T</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">g</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><mi>T</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">g</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T&#x27; \\mathsf{Alg} \\to T \\mathsf{Alg}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9463em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\" style=\"margin-right:0.0139em;\">Alg</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\" style=\"margin-right:0.0139em;\">Alg</span></span></span></span></span> that has a left adjoint.   So, the forgetful functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">k</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">f</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathsf{Rack} \\to \\mathsf{Shelf}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">Rack</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\" style=\"margin-right:0.0694em;\">Shelf</span></span></span></span></span> should have a left adjoint.</p>",
        "id": 605999218,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1782220346
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, that general statement is true: the algebra categories are locally finitely presentable and the forgetful functor preserves limits and filtered colimits because they're created on underlying sets, so it has a left adjoint.</p>",
        "id": 606027409,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Carlson",
        "timestamp": 1782226845
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wish I understood all that stuff.   But not enough to actually put energy into learning it!  <span aria-label=\"laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f606\" role=\"img\" title=\"laughing\">:laughing:</span></p>",
        "id": 606027831,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1782226943
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's always fun to hang on to a mystical incantation to chant at people.</p>",
        "id": 606031212,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Carlson",
        "timestamp": 1782227723
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In fact it's easy to write down the coequalizers that give you the left adjoint to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>T</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">g</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo><mi>T</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">g</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T&#x27;\\mathsf{Alg} \\to T\\mathsf{Alg}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9463em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\" style=\"margin-right:0.0139em;\">Alg</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\" style=\"margin-right:0.0139em;\">Alg</span></span></span></span></span>. It looks something like this: </p>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>T</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">g</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>↦</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">q</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msup><mi>T</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mi>T</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>⇉</mo><msup><mi>T</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mi>A</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(A: T\\mathsf{Alg}) \\mapsto \\mathrm{coeq} (T&#x27; T A \\rightrightarrows T&#x27; A)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\" style=\"margin-right:0.0139em;\">Alg</span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">↦</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0019em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">coeq</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel amsrm\">⇉</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0019em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> </p>\n<p>(the coequalizer being computed in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>T</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">g</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T&#x27;\\mathsf{Alg}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9463em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\" style=\"margin-right:0.0139em;\">Alg</span></span></span></span></span>), which I'm going to leave to your imagination what those two arrows are. (But you just follow your canonical nose.)</p>",
        "id": 606032231,
        "sender_full_name": "Todd Trimble",
        "timestamp": 1782227994
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's sort of like taking a \"tensor product\" <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>T</mi><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><msub><mo>∘</mo><mi>T</mi></msub><mi>A</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T&#x27; \\circ_T A</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9019em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7519em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3283em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 606032417,
        "sender_full_name": "Todd Trimble",
        "timestamp": 1782228045
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks everyone. If I ever get around to working any of this out I'll report back!</p>",
        "id": 606186026,
        "sender_full_name": "Chad Nester",
        "timestamp": 1782290816
    }
